cs.CR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper is about automatic identification of Indicators of Compromise (IOCs) using a neural-based sequence labelling model. This task falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it deals with detecting cyber-attacks. The proposed model uses natural language processing techniques, which suggests it could also belong to the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for sequence labelling indicates it could also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
